Vice President Biden will be hosting the first-ever Caribbean Energy Security Summit on January 26, 2015, in Washington, DC. The purpose of the summit is to promote a cleaner and more sustainable energy future in the Caribbean through improved energy governance, greater access to finance, and donor coordination. The summit will include remarks by the Vice President, an energy security roundtable with heads of government, and meetings with government officials, representatives from the private sector, and officials from multilateral institutions. This summit is part of the Caribbean Energy Security Initiative that the Vice President announced in June 2014 and is being organized by the White House, the State Department, the Atlantic Council, and the Council of the Americas. Further details will be provided soon.